    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_533222">As far as we know, no it is not terrorism.  If new facts come to light that we discover otherwise then it may later be classified as such.  I don't know why you brought either the issue of terrorism or racially profiling terrorists into this issue since it has nothing to do with either of them with the evidence that we have.<br />
<br />
Violent acts != terrorism<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Also, and I'm rarely this blunt when it comes to political issues, but blaming violence on guns is just plain stupid.<br />
<br />
For a moment lets just pretend that guns don't exist.  Perfect world, right?<br />
<br />
Well, no.  We still have bombs.  Making explosives is basic chemistry.  So the next logical step is to magically do away with bombs.  Poof, those are gone too.<br />
<br />
Oh wait.  We still have chemical weapons, the easiest of which to make is mustard gas.  Hell, they listed the ingredients on King of the Hill, so quite a few people know how to make that too.  Poof.  Chemical weapons are now imaginary as well.<br />
<br />
We still have crossbows/bows, swords, knives, throwing weapons (such as rocks), bludgeoning weapons (such as heavy sticks), incinerating weapons, electrical weapons, etc.<br />
<br />
My point is that if people want to kill people they will find a way, whether premeditated or not.  Getting rid of guns does not stop a murderer, as they will move to a different weapon of choice.<br />
<br />
<br />
I would like to declare as a personal note that I do not own any guns nor do I intend on ever owning a gun.  However, I believe in responsible gun ownership and I also believe that any degree of outlawing firearms would only make it harder for honest people to obtain them, not the dishonest.</div>
