    <div align="left" id="post_message_533236">It's a terrible, tragic thing, but it's the details which are emotionally traumatizing.<br />
<br />
On average over a hundred people die every day from car crashes, but we're desensitized to that. It didn't make the news and it wasn't anyone we knew, so it's just an emotionless statistic.<br />
<br />
I'm not trying to downplay the tragedy of this disaster or the heartache truly felt by those suffering loss - but I am saying that a hundred families yesterday lost a loved one in a fatal car accident, too, and their tragedy and heartache is just as real whether America at large knows, cares, or not.</div>
