</div>It's a good thing that I didn't use that argument, then.  My argument was not about banning guns (which, by the way, would only create an absolutely enormous black market with all the firearms that already exist in the country), but rather the fact that if guns weren't a thing at all... if they never existed... there are still many other ways to kill people, some of them even more effective than guns.<br />
<br />
Too many people miss the main issue whenever a tragedy like this occurs.  Guns were the method used, but not the cause.  Taking guns out of the equation does not magically make these people mentally healthy, good, upstanding citizens, it merely makes them consider alternate means of carrying out their plans.</div>
