    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_533312">What I'm advocating is that as it stands it's already illegal to carry concealed weapons without a permit, and the obtainment of said permit should (and everywhere that I know of does) require firearm handling training. I'm not going to go as far as to say that everyone would be expected to have police officer level training, but I do expect them to have been through training which lays the groundwork for what to do in this kind of situation.<br />
<br />
I think this is the primary issue I have with the anti-gun mindset: for some reason there is this idea that you can just waltz down to the local grocery store and put a glock in your buggy next to your milk and eggs. It's not like that at all. You have to pass a background check, obtain your permit, wait three days, etc. (I realize not all gun laws are standard across all states, but bear with me here.)<br />
<br />
The exception to these checks and balances is when you buy a gun off the black market. Which - guess what? - is illegal anyway, so is a moot point when it comes to gun control.</div>
