    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_533341">The current gun debate has way to high a level of absolutism on both sides for me to feel confident in progress being achieved.  One area that some posters have touched on where I really feel bipartisan traction could be achieved is mental health.  We as a society need to figure a better way at spotting.g at risk people and getting them help and/or making sure they can't hurt others.  Most of the folks in these sprees have given warning signs before they went over the edge but the right decision wasn't made.  For anyone who didn't read the &quot;I am Adam Lanzas Mother&quot; link please do.  It will give you a window into what many parents with mentally ill children are dealing with.</div>
